commit ac1bf5a7bce078859ec397d68941e930e5edf975
Author: Martin Robillard <prmr@gmx.com>
Date:   Thu Jun 23 14:14:24 2022 -0400

    I#466 Remove global management of class diagram viewers
    
    Multiple instances of ClassDiagramViewers were managed as a global
    variable within DiagramType, which made it very difficult to keep track
    of the state and led to memory leaks. Now, only a single "active"
    diagram viewer is managed by the RenderingFacade.

commit 3b9f9f7a806f308e5c062fe7c2e679b8f2b8848c
Author: Martin Robillard <prmr@gmx.com>
Date:   Mon Jun 13 16:05:24 2022 -0400

    I#466 Extract Viewer Interface
    
    NodeViewers and EdgeViewers share much functionality. This commit
    creates a new superinterface DiagramElementRenderer to collect the
    services of both subhierarchies. In this initial commit the interface
    has only one method, but the idea is to progressively move up more
    methods.

2	1	src/org/jetuml/viewers/edges/CallEdgeViewer.java

commit a1d6a9f3df8b9c18013a8fdb52dbe5709bf8a275
Author: Martin Robillard <prmr@gmx.com>
Date:   Wed May 4 13:29:02 2022 -0400

    Issue #375 Replace use of Direction with NodeSide
    
    The type Direction allows all 360 degrees of the circle, which is too
    broad for the use made in Layouter, which is restricted to the four
    cardinal directions. I defined a separate type, NodeSide, to describe
    this data.

commit 0fc6e43f3c1ac676b93034c0f8980fc8b58d56e0
Author: Maddy Lecsek <madelyn.lecsek@mail.mcgill.ca>
Date:   Mon May 2 15:43:08 2022 -0400

    #375 Use EdgeStorage to draw selection handles and remove unused imports
    
    Add a method drawSelectionHandles(pSelected, pGraphics) to
    DiagramCanvas. This method is called by paintPanel() and checks if the
    current diagram is a class diagram. If so, the method delegates the draw
    selection handles functionality to ClassDiagramViewer.
    ClassDiagramViewer uses EdgeStorage to get the start and end connection
    points of a stored edge when drawing the selection handles.
    
    Remove unused or duplicate imports.

commit 8506d3e0b3db5b056767891131936d38534a8029
Author: Maddy Lecsek <madelyn.lecsek@mail.mcgill.ca>
Date:   Sat Apr 23 14:54:57 2022 -0400

    #375 Added Layouter, ClassDiagramViewer, and StoredEdgeViewer
    
    In order for each diagram to be associated with its own unique storage,
    ClassDiagramViewer has been converted into a stateful diagram viewer
    which is unique to each class diagram .This way, each ClassDiagramViewer
    aggregates an EdgeStorage object and a StoredEdgeViewer which is used to
    draw stored edges. When drawing edges, ClassDiagramViewer is responsible
    for invoking Layouter to plan the edges in the diagram.
    ClassDiagramViewer also calls on its StoredEdgeViewer constituent to
    draw the diagrams edges using EdgeStorage.
    
    DiagramType maps diagrams to their DiagramViewer which is accessible
    using the public method viewerFor(Diagram
    pDiagram). DiagramType also maintains a map of class diagrams and their
    ClassDiagramViewers. So, viewerFor(Diagram pDiagram) returns the unique
    ClassDiagramViewer for pDiagram if it
    is a class diagram.
    
    Each ClassDiagramViewer aggregates a Layouter object which is
    responsible for planning and storing the paths
    of edges in the diagram. This features is invoked through Layouters
    only public method: layout(pDiagram).
    
    Add tests for ClassDiagramViewer, StoredEdgeviewer, and Layouter.

commit ef599d87aa4baabb7095c30b46b5e1180d462672
Author: prmr <prmr@gmx.com>
Date:   Tue Jan 18 08:01:15 2022 -0500

    #446 Use default font size in font-sensitive tests
    
    Some tests of the diagram layout are sensitive to the font size. The
    font size is stored in the system properties. Before the test, we cache
    the current font size, then set the default one for the tests, and
    restore the user's font size once the tests are over.

Author: delphinepilon <delphine.pilon@icloud.com>
Date:   Wed Nov 17 16:47:35 2021 -0500

    Make the segmented edge label positioning without overlap consistent.
    
    In order to avoid the label overlapping with the segments of a segmented edge, we introduce the method isStepUp which takes in an edge and returns a boolean representing whether the edge represents a visual step up or a step down. This information is relevant in the method getAttachmentPoint to unify the behaviour of the label's position with respect to vertical middle segment edges. As of now, there should be less overlap between the middle label of a segmented edge and its segments.

commit ade6fd655de542bafb2690a4c02b3ed9df884ad4
Author: delphinepilon <delphine.pilon@icloud.com>
Date:   Thu Nov 4 12:34:13 2021 -0400

    #375 Add a NodeStorage, unit tests, and a performance test.
    
    A NodeStorage was added to each NodeViewer to improve the performance of DiagramViewer.draw(diagram). For each call to NodeViewer.getBounds(node), if the NodeStorage is deactivated, then the bounds will be computed as returned. If the NodeStorage is activated, then it will first check whether the bounds have already been computed, and if so, it will return them directly. Otherwise, it will compute the bounds to be returned and store them for future reference. As soon as the NodeStorage is deactivated, it is cleared.
    
    A performance test was added to notice the benefits of this change.
    
    Unit tests are included to test the new behaviour.

    #439 Add mini-framework for writing diagram layout tests.
    
    The class AbstractTestDiagramLayout is the intended superclass for all

    layout tested by one class. The convenience methods are available in the
    abstract class. The class TestLayoutObjectDiagram is a stub.

commit 30a9afab385a84db75e29f5e54fedbd2cce30b2f
Author: prmr <prmr@gmx.com>

    #439 Add TestPersistenceService2
    
    This class adds a test that focuses specifically on testing that the
    persistence service works, without verifying the details of the diagram,
    which will be moved to specialized layout test classes.
    
    The class is named ...2 to avoid a class in the revision history. The

commit d360abae910c50bcba882b3b76b0702b3083ed09
Author: prmr <prmr@gmx.com>
Date:   Thu Apr 29 15:30:42 2021 -0400

    #427 Remove node's position as properties
    
    The x and y values for the position of a node are no longer managed as
    node properties. This design decisions created a special case that adds
    unnecessary complexity and prevents the Point class from being
    immutable.
    
    From this point on, the position of a node is solely managed through
    using the position() and moveTo(...) methods on Node.

commit 4009e94a850c965e1d4538d9e2d1ca6726cdf9c2
Author: farihatanjin <fariha.anika@mail.mcgill.ca>
Date:   Sun Mar 7 23:33:57 2021 -0500

    #416 refactor edge constraints checking
    
    ConstraintSet is now stored as a private static final field in each
    diagram builder. This reduces object creation by eliminating the need to
    create and merge new ConstraintSet objects each time canAdd is
    called. For this reason, I removed the `merge` method in ConstraintSet
    which is no longer necessary.
    The ConstraintSet field can be accessed by method
    getEdgeConstraints() which simply returns the set of constraints. I
    see no encapsulation issue in doing so since there is no method
    available to modify contents of a ConstraintSet which will be
    returned.
    Satisfied takes in the canAdd parameters in order to check the
    conditions while keeping the code simple.

commit adb9e2ac1c7be29abace310a8ea8a68af2485787
Author: prmr <prmr@gmx.com>
Date:   Tue Feb 23 14:02:10 2021 -0500

    #416 Refactor constraint about edge end in sequence diagram
    
    The case where trying to create a constructor edge was implemented as a
    special case in constraints, where the constraint was only added to the
    constraint set if the call could be a legal constructor call. This
    divergence from the design, where all constraints are stored in a set,
    was creating an obstacle to the future improvement of the constraint
    management. With this change, all constraints are implemented as
    predicates.

2	6	src/ca/mcgill/cs/jetuml/diagram/builder/SequenceDiagramBuilder.java
11	3	src/ca/mcgill/cs/jetuml/diagram/builder/constraints/SequenceDiagramEdgeConstraints.java
4	4	test/ca/mcgill/cs/jetuml/diagram/builder/constraints/TestSequenceDiagramEdgeConstraints.java

commit 96064413ec1a6d4e23ea7e213f3d3775415291e5
Author: prmr <prmr@gmx.com>
Date:   Mon Feb 22 16:36:28 2021 -0500

    #416 Move creation of ConstructorCall to SequenceDiagramBuilder
    
    When a user attempts to create a constructor call, they use the normal
    "CallEdge" creation tool from the tool bar. This design decision was to
    avoid forcing the user to use two very similar tools to create call and
    constructor edges. However, internally if a constructor call is created,
    a ConstructorEdge must be used, so it's necessary to convert the
    original CallEdge to a Constructor Edge. This was initially done in the
    DiagramCanvasController, leading to a special case and coupling with the
    SequenceDiagram Builder. To avoid this design weakness, the conversion
    from CallEdge to ConstructorEdge is moved to the SequenceDiagramBuilder.

7	3	src/ca/mcgill/cs/jetuml/diagram/builder/SequenceDiagramBuilder.java
0	8	src/ca/mcgill/cs/jetuml/gui/DiagramCanvasController.java
3	3	test/ca/mcgill/cs/jetuml/diagram/builder/TestSequenceDiagramBuilder.java

commit 8c6b2a790255028bb0ab007999227ce14ec8d18f
Author: prmr <prmr@gmx.com>
Date:   Thu Dec 17 17:36:16 2020 -0500

    #399 Extract geometric intersections calculation to utility class
    
    There are currently two places in the code where a Direction object is
    used to compute the intersection between a line that starts at the
    center of a shape with the contour of the shape. These computations are
    complex and related to geometry, so they would be best encapsulated
    within a class of the geometry package, where their parallel structure
    will be more evident. This will also facilitate improving diagram
    rendering by having a well-defined place to put intersection
    calculations for all shapes, so that we can add them for more complex
    shapes (such as rounded rectangles and ellipses) later.
